    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I use the `truffle-hdwallet-provider-privkey`, along with `nonce-tracker` to avoid issues with load-balanced clients. See my snippet of my `truffle.js`:\r\n```js\r\nconst Web3Utils = require('web3-utils');\r\nconst HDWalletProvider = require(\"truffle-hdwallet-provider-privkey\");\r\nconst NonceTrackerSubprovider = require(\"web3-provider-engine/subproviders/nonce-tracker\");\r\n\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  web3Utils: Web3Utils,\r\n  networks: {\r\n    ropsten: {\r\n      provider: () => {\r\n        let wallet = new HDWalletProvider(\r\n          \"<pk>\", \r\n          \"<client url>\"\r\n        );\r\n        let nonceTracker = new NonceTrackerSubprovider();\r\n        wallet.engine._providers.unshift(nonceTracker);\r\n        nonceTracker.setEngine(wallet.engine);\r\n        return wallet;\r\n      },\r\n      network_id: 3,\r\n      gas: 4700000,\r\n      gasPrice: 30000000000,\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n  solc: {\r\n    optimizer: {\r\n      enabled: true,\r\n      runs: 200\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n};\r\n```\r\nEDIT: Using a nonce tracker is ideal for when running against clients like Infura for example. But if you're just using your own single client, just return the `HDWalletProvider`.",
